file.content:
//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_rekon}

NOTE: This operation reports which canonical members are present under a
hallmark or reliquary subtree in
{rbtgi_repository}
via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.
Raw presence enumeration — no health classification (use {rbtgo_hallmark_tally} for that).

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons over two domains, each backed by a distinct procedure:

* `rbfl_rekon_hallmark` — basenames present under a hallmark subtree
* `rbfl_rekon_reliquary` — tool images present under a reliquary stamp's subtree

Rekon over the legacy enshrinement domain is intentionally omitted: an enshrinement is a single image per anchor (1-deep), so no presence table is meaningful — {rbtgo_image_audit} covers the catalog and {rbtgo_image_retrieve} covers retrieval.

== Hallmark Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons basenames under a hallmark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_hallmark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Usage: rbw-irh <hallmark>"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Hallmarks Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled from `RBGC_GAR_CATEGORY_HALLMARKS`, the token `rbi_hm`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/`
.. For each retained `<hallmark>/<basename>` package, {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages.tags/list[GAR REST API: tags.list] for the package and {rbbc_require} at least one tag returned (HTTP 200 with non-empty `.tags[]`). Skip packages with zero tags — these are post-jettison walking-dead awaiting the depot's cleanup policy (see {rbtgo_depot_levy} step *Create Container Repository*). Filtering at this read site decouples the display from GAR's lazy reclamation cadence.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK_ROWS»` as `«HALLMARK» «BASENAME»` pairs derived from the live-tagged entries (a 2-deep enumeration)

//axhos_step
. *Filter to Input Hallmark*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PRESENT»` as the set of basenames in `«HALLMARK_ROWS»` whose hallmark equals `«INPUT_HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PRESENT»` is empty: "Hallmark not found: «INPUT_HALLMARK»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
table header `BASENAME | EXISTS | PACKAGE-PATH`
.. For each canonical basename in the order
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
{rbtga_ark_vouch},
`attest`,
{rbtga_ark_pouch},
{rbtga_ark_diags}:
... {rbbc_store}
`«MARK»` as `yes` if `«BASENAME»` ∈ `«PRESENT»`, else `no`
... {rbbc_store}
`«PATH»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/«BASENAME»` when `«MARK»` = `yes`, else the literal `(absent)`
... {rbbc_show}
row `«BASENAME» | «MARK» | «PATH»`

== Reliquary Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons tool images under a reliquary stamp:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_STAMP»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Usage: rbw-irr <stamp>"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Reliquaries Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»` from `RBGL_RELIQUARIES_ROOT` (kindled from `RBGC_GAR_CATEGORY_RELIQUARIES`, the token `rbi_rq`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/`
.. For each retained `<stamp>/<tool>` package, {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages.tags/list[GAR REST API: tags.list] for the package and {rbbc_require} at least one tag returned (HTTP 200 with non-empty `.tags[]`). Skip packages with zero tags — these are post-jettison walking-dead awaiting the depot's cleanup policy (see {rbtgo_depot_levy} step *Create Container Repository*). Filtering at this read site decouples the display from GAR's lazy reclamation cadence.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` as `«STAMP» «TOOL»` pairs derived from the live-tagged entries (a 2-deep enumeration)

//axhos_step
. *Filter to Input Stamp*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PRESENT»` as the set of tools in `«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` whose stamp equals `«INPUT_STAMP»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PRESENT»` is empty: "Reliquary stamp not found: «INPUT_STAMP»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
table header `TOOL | EXISTS | PACKAGE-PATH`
.. For each canonical reliquary tool in the order `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `skopeo`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«MARK»` as `yes` if `«TOOL»` ∈ `«PRESENT»`, else `no`
... {rbbc_store}
`«PATH»` as `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/«INPUT_STAMP»/«TOOL»` when `«MARK»` = `yes`, else the literal `(absent)`
... {rbbc_show}
row `«TOOL» | «MARK» | «PATH»`

//axhoc_completion
Each procedure completes successfully when the canonical row set has been displayed for the input identifier.
A subtree with no matching row across the canon is treated as the "not present" signal and reported as a fatal — empty subtrees do not yield empty tables.
The operation does not classify health; that is the role of {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_delete}

NOTE: This operation jettisons a single image tag from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

`rbfl_jettison` is locator-generic: the same procedure backs
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark members,
reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
The package path embedded in the
{rbst_locator}
selects the domain — the procedure itself does not branch.

NOTE: To delete an entire {rbtga_ark} (the full `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` subtree — every basename including `image`, `about`, `vouch`, and any `pouch`/`diags`/`attest` tags present), use {rbtgo_ark_abjure} instead.

NOTE: Jettisoning an interior member of a reliquary subtree (e.g., a single tool image) leaves a hole in an otherwise-coherent set. The operator accepts this piecemeal-by-image semantic; recovery is nuclear: re-run {rbtgo_depot_inscribe} to restore the full reliquary corpus. The operation provides no integrity guard against such interior holes.

The
{rbtr_director}
jettisons an image by {rbst_locator}:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_locator}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `package-path:tag` format
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Locator parameter required (package-path:tag)"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected package-path:tag"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PACKAGE_PATH»` as portion before the final colon (e.g., `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image`, `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/syft`, `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAG»` as portion after the final colon
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PACKAGE_PATH»` is empty: "Package path is empty in locator"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«TAG»` is empty: "Tag is empty in locator"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Jettison*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Will jettison: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Jettison Tag*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«PACKAGE_PATH»/manifests/«TAG»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if jettison fails: "Jettison failed with HTTP «STATUS_CODE»"
.. NOTE: V2 DELETE-by-tag has producer-side asymmetric semantics. For single-platform pushes (`docker push`), the tag points to a single image manifest; DELETE removes it, the package becomes empty, and GAR drops the package container from `ListPackages`. For multi-platform pushes (`docker buildx --push`, `skopeo copy --all`), the tag points to an OCI image index referencing N per-platform child manifests; DELETE removes only the index, leaving the N children as untagged orphan content. The package container persists in `ListPackages` because it still holds those untagged child manifests.
.. NOTE: The orphan-children residue is reclaimed autonomously by the depot's GAR cleanup policy — see {rbtgo_depot_levy} step *Create Container Repository* for the policy install, schema-verification sources, and cadence semantics. User-facing display surfaces ({rbtgo_hallmark_tally} and {rbtgo_image_rekon}) filter out packages with zero live tags, so tooling output reflects the correct post-jettison state immediately even though GAR-side reclamation is lazy. External observers querying GAR REST `ListPackages` directly will see the walking-dead package container until the cleanup policy's next run.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_locator}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Jettisoned or nonexistent: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the tag has been jettisoned from the registry and the jettisoned message is displayed.
The locator-generic shape means a hallmark member, a reliquary tool image, or an enshrinement image are all deleted by the same call — domain identity lives in the locator's package path, not in branched logic.

